1. Install Python

-> go to your Terminal/Command Prompt

2. To check your Python
C:\users\X>python -version

3. Create a virtual enviroment in Python
C:\users\X>python -m venv env

-m venv = virtual enviroment is created
env= name of the virtual enviroment

4. Activate your virtual enviroment
C:\users\X>env\Scripts\activate

5. Install Selenium
C:\users\X>pip install selenium

6. Create your Script-File
C:\users\X>echo. >webscraper.py

7. Open the File
C:\users\X>webscraper.py

8. Lets write in the webscraper.py-File
from selenium import webdriver

url='LINK'
browser=webdriver.Chrome()browser.get(url)

browser.find_element_by_xpath(XPATH FROM WEB-INSPECTION/HTML).click()

9. let's run the Webpage/File
C:\users\KLubina>python webscraper.py
